  "updated_summary": "Mark Wiens, in a green t-shirt, introduces a Chicago hot dog stand, opting for a classic 'formerly five-cent meal' over the 'DOGZILLA' option. He and Derek Robinson, in a black t-shirt, are then seen enjoying Chicago-style hot dogs, with Derek exclaiming \"Let's go!\" as lively brass music and eating sounds commence, leading Mark to declare, \"That's Chicago right there.\" An aerial urban view with train tracks and buildings, accompanied by train and mechanical sounds, transitions to a street view of 'JOHNNIE'S RED HOTS FRIES SHAKES'. Mark Wiens, standing outside, expresses extreme excitement to try the Italian beef sandwich, calling it \"the spot.\" A cook in a white shirt and gloves is shown assembling a hot dog with toppings. Later, Mark, wearing a 'Not Spicy Not Eating' t-shirt, stands outside Johnnie's Beef, highlighting it as the place for \"a beef\" according to \"true, extreme, die-hard food lovers,\" with the 'JOHNNIE'S RED HOTS FRIES SHAKES' and 'ITALIAN LEMONADE' sign visible. The bustling storefront with outdoor seating and patrons is shown under the late afternoon sun, described by Mark as a \"well-oiled machine\" and a \"shrine of Italian beef.\" Amidst background chatter, a gloved hand prepares a hot dog with mustard, relish, and chopped onions. A man in a blue t-shirt from 'TENNESSEE BREW WORKS' near the entrance states his preference for a \"combo dry sweet\" Italian beef sandwich with sweet peppers, explaining, \"I don't like any juice on the bread.\""
